The error ConnectionRefusedError: [Errno 111] Connection refused occurred because the client program attempted to connect to the server at localhost on port 12345, but no server was running and listening on that port at the time. When the connect() method was executed, the operating system checked for a service accepting connections on the specified address and port, found none, and therefore rejected the connection request. In this case, the error happened because client_2.py was started before server.py, so there was no active server available to accept the client's connection.
